# Cursor Rules for nest-temporal

## What this project is

nest-temporal is a NestJS dynamic module wrapping Temporal.io. It provides decorator-based activity registration (@Worker, @Activity), automatic worker discovery, a global TemporalClientService, and a scoped @InjectWorkflowClient() decorator (like BullMQ's @InjectQueue).

## Code style

- TypeScript strict mode with experimentalDecorators
- All public exports go through src/index.ts — users import from 'nest-temporal' only
- Decorators use SetMetadata from @nestjs/common
- Services use standard NestJS patterns: @Injectable(), OnModuleInit, OnApplicationShutdown
- JSDoc required on all exported symbols
- Log messages use emoji prefixes (✅ ❌ 🚀 📦 🔍)
- Errors during connection/startup are logged, NOT thrown (graceful degradation)

## Key files

- src/temporal.module.ts — DynamicModule with forRoot(), forRootAsync(), registerClient()
- src/services/temporal-client.service.ts — global Temporal client
- src/services/workflow-client.ts — task-queue-scoped client (BullMQ Queue equivalent)
- src/services/temporal-discovery.service.ts — auto-discovers @Worker/@Activity at startup
- src/services/temporal-worker.service.ts — manages Temporal Worker lifecycle
- src/decorators/ — @Worker(), @Activity(), @InjectWorkflowClient()
- src/constants.ts — injection tokens and metadata keys

## When editing this codebase

- Run `npm test` after any change — all tests must pass
- Run `npx tsc -p tsconfig.build.json --noEmit` for type-checking
- Tests are in test/ directory, use Jest + @nestjs/testing
- Temporal SDK is mocked in tests — no real server needed
- If adding a new export, add it to src/index.ts AND update llms.txt / llms-full.txt

## When generating code that USES nest-temporal

- All imports come from 'nest-temporal' (never subpaths)
- Two ways to start workflows:
  - Global: inject TemporalClientService, call startWorkflow(type, id, args, taskQueue)
  - Scoped: TemporalModule.registerClient('queue'), then @InjectWorkflowClient('queue') → WorkflowClient
- @Worker() classes MUST also have @Injectable() and be registered as providers
- Workflows are plain Temporal files using proxyActivities() — they do NOT use NestJS DI
- workflowsPath should use require.resolve() at the decorator site
- For tests, mock WorkflowClient with getWorkflowClientToken('queue') as the provide token
